securepoll-votereligibility-lists-info:
Eligible voters may also be listed explicitly. There are three lists:
* The ''{{int:securepoll-votereligibility-voter}}'' is a list of voters who are allowed to vote, if they also meet the basic requirements defined above. This list is often populated automatically.
* The ''{{int:securepoll-votereligibility-include}}'' is a list of voters who are allowed to vote regardless of the basic requirements or the eligibility list.
* The ''{{int:securepoll-votereligibility-exclude}}'' is a list of voters who are not allowed to vote, regardless of any other lists.

securepoll-stv-help-text: The following table describes the calculations that happened in order to achieve the result above. In each round of calculation, the candidate(s) who achieved more votes than the quota are declared elected. Their surplus votes above the quota are redistributed to the remaining candidates. If nobody achieves the quota, the lowest ranking candidate is eliminated and their votes are redistributed to the remaining candidates. To understand this better, please refer to [https://web.archive.org/web/20210225045400/https://prfound.org/resources/reference/reference-meek-rule/ this link].
